You are a social media content template specialist for sports teams. Create engaging, professional templates based on the user's request.

Template Type: {{ $json.templateType }}
Request Details: {{ $json.body }}
Specific Content: {{ $json.templateContent || 'General template requested' }}

Guidelines:
- Keep templates under 280 characters for multi-platform use
- Include placeholder variables in {{brackets}} for dynamic content
- Use appropriate emojis (1-2 maximum)
- Include relevant hashtags
- Make it sound authentic and energetic
- Provide 3 variations of the template

Provide the output as JSON with this structure:
{
  "templates": [
    {
      "variation": 1,
      "content": "Template content here with {{variables}}",
      "hashtags": "#hashtag1 #hashtag2",
      "platform_notes": "Best for Instagram/Twitter/Facebook"
    },
    // ... 2 more variations
  ]
}

parameters.jsCode:
// Parse AI-generated templates and prepare for storage
const requestData = $('parse-template-request').item;
const aiResponse = $json.choices[0].message.content;

let templates = [];
try {
  const parsedResponse = JSON.parse(aiResponse);
  templates = parsedResponse.templates || [];
} catch (error) {
  // Fallback: try to extract templates from plain text
  const lines = aiResponse.split('\n').filter(line => line.trim());
  templates = [
    {
      variation: 1,
      content: lines[0] || 'Template generation failed',
      hashtags: '#sports #team',
      platform_notes: 'General use'
    }
  ];
}

// Prepare template data for storage
const templateData = templates.map((template, index) => ({
  requestId: requestData.requestId,
  templateType: requestData.templateType,
  clientId: requestData.clientId,
  variation: template.variation || (index + 1),
  content: template.content,
  hashtags: template.hashtags,
  platformNotes: template.platform_notes,
  createdDate: new Date().toISOString(),
  status: 'generated',
  usageCount: 0,
  fromRequest: {
    email: requestData.fromEmail,
    name: requestData.fromName,
    originalSubject: requestData.subject
  }
}));

return templateData.map(template => ({ json: template }));

